Package it.polimi.ingsw.server.model

Class Table

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.server.model.Table
class Table extends Object
Represents a snapshot of the game's playing board, including players. This is essentially a data holder manipulated by the state machine.

  • Constructor Details

    • Table

      Table()
      Creates a new Table. Every list/container is initialized and empty except for the islands and professors. Mother Nature is placed on the first island. The random positioning will be done inside the correct phase of the game.

    • addPlayer

      Table addPlayer(Player player, int entranceSize, int numTowers, TowerColor towerColor)
      Seat the given Player at this table. Together with the Player a Board is added.
      Parameters:
      player - this Player
      entranceSize - the entrance size of the Player's Board
      numTowers - the number of Towers in this Player's Board
      towerColor - the color of this player's Towers
      Returns:
      a new Table with the new changes
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if any parameter is null
      IllegalArgumentException - if entranceSize and numTowers are less than or equal to zero
      IllegalArgumentException - if a player with the same username is already seated at the table

    • removePlayer

      Table removePlayer(String username)
      Remove the Player with the specified username and its Board from this Table. If no matching Player can be found, nothing is done.
      Parameters:
      username - the username of the Player to remove
      Returns:
      a new Table with the new changes
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if username is null
